def: The institution, government, or authority of a church. [R.] Bp.Pearson.
A state of permanent rigidity or contraction of the muscles,generally of the flexor muscles.
The fur of the coypu. See Coypu.
Of or pertaining to a state before consciousness.
An instrument which registers meteorologic phases orconditions.
A viceroy; a governor of a subah; also, a native captain in theBritish native army. [India]
One who is versed in atmology.
